President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has issued a memorandum delegating authority to the Secretary of State under section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. This authority allows the Secretary of State to direct the drawdown of up to $1 billion in defense articles and services, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. The Secretary of State is also authorized to make the necessary determinations required under this section to facilitate the drawdown. The memorandum directs the publication of this delegation of authority in the Federal Register.